minister before fleeing the report said 
lt col cresencio maralit spokesman for the philippine 
constabulary said the incident occurred early sunday in the village 
of rano about 640 miles southeast of manila 
maralit said many of the villagers had joined an anticommunist 
vigilante group and had refused to pay revolutionary taxes to 
the communist new peoples army 
according to maralit about 40 members of the ubo and bagobo 
tribes had gathered inside a united church of christ chapel for 
morning worship when about 100 guerrillas arrived 
