meanwhile the food and drug administration today announced 
approval of a drug to treat an eye infection in aids patients that 
can lead to blindness it is the fourth drug to be approved for 
treatment of aids or an aidsrelated condition 
the drug ganciclovir has been widely available for several 
months to aids patients with the eye infection cytomegalovirus 
retinitis under a special fda category called treatment ind 
that allows distribution of promising drugs to the gravely ill while 
safety and effectiveness research continues 
about 20 percent of aids patients develop the eye infection 
syntex corp of palo alto calif will market the drug under the 
name cytovene 
the fda also announced treatment ind status for an 
experimental protein rerythropoietin to treat severe anemia that 
weakens nearly half of the 20000 patients taking the antiviral 
drug azt 
fda commissioner frank young said the two actions reflect the 
agencys commitment to getting promising new drugs to aids victims 
quickly he said that while there still is no cure for the disease 
these two drugs and others recently approved for commercial release 
and treatment inds can extend and improve the lives of aids 
patients making early diagnosis more important 
the gao evaluated 13 national forecasts of the cumulative number 
of aids cases through the end of 1991 and found a range of 
predictions from 85000 to 750000 cases the report looked only at 
the number of potential aids cases not the number of people who 
test positive for the aidscausing human immunodeficiency virus but 
show no symptoms of aids 
projections of the spread of acquired immune deficiency syndrome 
are important because they are used in deciding how much money is 
spent on aids education research projects and public health care 
services for aids patients 
also if faulty forecasting is underestimating the heterosexual 
spread of aids as the report concludes the result may be luring 
a significant number of americans into a false sense of security 
wyden said 
sunday editions of the washington post said cdc officials 
acknowledged serious underreporting of aids cases but said gao 
projections were too high 
the report blamed the undercounting on a variety of factors 
including the absence of data on the size of risk groups the 
definition of what constitutes an aids case reliance on incomplete 
surveillance data and the undercounting of heterosexuals at risk 
the report said cdc must get more uptodate and accurate 
information about the risk groups if it hopes to improve its 
projections 
earlir this month a university of chicago study also said cdc 
may be significantly underestimating the number of americans with 
aids the study attributed some of the undercounting to affluent 
victims who are treated discreetly by physicians who do not report 
cases of the disease 
aids is spread by close contact with blood blood products or 
semen from infected people its chief victims are homosexual men and 
intravenous drug users 
as of may 31 1989 aids had been diagnosed in 97193 americans 
of whom more than half or 56468 have died since june 1 1981 
according to the cdc no one is known to have recovered from aids 
