attempt to silence the mississippi river fortress 126 years ago 
and at brices cross roads in lee county scene of a textbook 
attack by confederate gen nathan bedford forrests cavalry 
historians recently replaced 99 markers to unknown southern dead 
with 102 stones bearing the names of rebel soldiers known to have 
been killed in the june 10 1864 battle 
