times by dervishlike drummer duffy jackson drove up the tempo the 
orchestra performed a memorable count basie remembrance suite in 
honor of its jaunty founder carmen bradford the bands vocalist 
sang a powerful and exciting young and foolish 
then came the highlight the audience had been waiting for 
williams came back on stage and shouted several blues songs his 
voice welling up to match the power of the basie bunch 
happy birthday joe williams and many more 
by william gillen associated press writer 
