here is a text of former speaker jim wrights 
statement on his decision to resign his house seat effective friday 
and not seek reelection 
since announcing that i would retire from the house of 
representatives at the end of this month i have received thousands 
of written and verbal requests from people in my district imploring 
me to reconsider 
some have spoken of writing my name in on the special election 
ballot and some others even have begun circulating petitions to 
place my name on the ballot 
naturally i have been moved by such gracious and spontaneous 
expressions of support i did not encourage these entreaties but 
out of profound respect and affection for the wonderful people who 
have been coming to me i did not peremptorily dismiss their ideas 
i heard them out 
as deeply as i appreciate the devoted friendship which impels 
these sincere petitions i must conclude that i was right in 
announcing my retirement from congress 
independent polling data have made it very clear that i could be 
reelected these demonstrations of strong bipartisan support are 
truly gratifying but i feel that i probably have done as much good 
as i can do in congress at the present time and should look to the 
next phase of my life 
it is best for the institution and best for the people whom ive 
served that i step aside now and make room for others 
thirtyfour and a half years is a very long time and i have been 
richly blessed 
to seek and gain the splendid honor of a public endorsement one 
more time would be vainglorious to do so without intending to serve 
for a prolonged period would be pointless 
to postpone the moment when another may begin would be a 
disservice 
i do not foreclose the possibility that at some future time and 
some other way i may again be of service to our nation but not in 
elective office 
as for now betty and i are ready to enjoy a period of private 
life i will not be inactive but i hope to be selective and pursue 
a slightly less hectic pace than at present i have received perhaps 
65 or 70 speaking invitations for example and have accepted five 
or six i am also considering some limited business and professional 
relationships and some invitations to write i will have an office 
in fort worth 
if i should live to be 100 i shall never cease to be grateful to 
the people of my area and to my colleagues in congress who have made 
it possible for me to do whatever good ive been able to do for our 
country and to have the joy of doing it 
</TEXT>
