<TEXT>
miscovich left school in the 11th grade never went to college 
yet the knowledge of geology and mining he picked up on his own is 
so recognized that he has served for years in the winter months as a 
consultant to mining companies inspecting potential digging sites 
around the globe 
he could have made a fine living at that alone it isnt need or 
greed he says that draws him and his wife here every summer from 
their comfortable winter home in orange calif 
their home here is typical of an alaska mining camp it is small 
tinroofed its plumbing uncertain its dooryard cluttered with old 
wagon wheels moose antlers remains of mining equipment 
