ninthgrade students who go off to boarding schools 
prep for prep has a 19 million budget for its preparatory 
program counseling tutoring and administrative costs its covered 
by grants from foundations and corporations and gifts from 
individuals state and city money accounts for 2 percent of the 
budget 
about onequarter of those accepted into prep for prep drop out 
of the 14month program but 95 percent of those who are accepted 
into private schools complete their secondary education there 
