<TEXT>
sears roebuck and co said today it will keep its 
6000employee merchandise group in illinois but move it to a 
chicago suburb we believe this chicagoland location will serve 
the best interests of our company and its shareholders for decades 
to come chairman edward brennan said in a statement released 
before a morning news conference 
we anticipate that the move to the new facility will begin in 
2 to 3 years he said 
the site is in hoffman estates 20 miles northwest of chicago 
last fall the nations largest retailer announced a 
restructuring plan that included selling the 110story sears tower 
the worlds tallest building and shifting the merchandise group 
and its 6000 employees to less costly quarters 
the announcement set off a bidding war between illinois and 
sunbelt states especially north carolina and texas 
the chicago tribune said illinois offered an incentive package 
worth an estimated 61 million to lure the merchandise group to a 
200acre site in hoffman estates the newspaper said local tax 
breaks to sears will be worth an estimated 178 million 
the total proposal that was worked out is extremely competitive 
with alternative sites brennan said 
the hoffman estates site is part of an undeveloped 1300 acres 
north of the northwest tollway at illinois 59 
sears said it had signed a contract to purchase 700 acres along 
the tollway including an outdoor music theater poplar creek sears 
said the theater will continue operating 
the hoffman estates parcel was selected from about 50 sites in 
the chicago area and other states brennan said 
sears estimates that building a campusstyle facility in hoffman 
estates will cost about 220 million the development will 
eventually generate an estimated 11 million a year in property 
taxes 
brennan said future commercial development of the site also is 
planned 
the tribune and the chicago suntimes said the deal was cemented 
sunday after talks between illinois gov james r thompson and 
brennan 
when the merchandise group move is completed about 600 employees 
of sears corporate staff will remain in the downtown sears tower 
the company said 
